|> spoken-for-near
    source=img/near-a.svg
    source=img/near-b.svg
    source=img2/far-diagnostic-only.svg

Select both source paths and run Writerly: Move File Under Cursor.
Enter img or img2.

For missing-file warning testing, source=img2/far-diagnostic-only.svg should
warn. The file exists only in far/img2/, while near/img2/ exists but does not
contain that filename.

Expected result:
- img/near-a.svg and img/near-b.svg move to near/img/ or near/img2/.
- The two source attributes change to img/near-a.svg and img/near-b.svg, or
img2/near-a.svg and img2/near-b.svg.
- far/img/ or far/img2/ is ignored because it is closer to the far topmost
Writerly root.
